tool /tuːl/

(tools) 

1. N-COUNT A tool is any instrument or simple piece of equipment that you hold in your hands and use to do a particular kind of work. For example, spades, hammers, and knives are all tools. 工具 

例： I find the best tool for the purpose is a pair of shears. 我发现达到这一目的的最好工具是一把大剪刀。 

2. N-COUNT You can refer to anything that you use for a particular purpose as a particular type of tool . 方法 

例： Writing is a good tool for expressing feelings. 写作是表达情感的一种好方法。

